    "In AI-focused tasks, they are supposed to help people notice when the AI does something wrong, whereas in image-focused tasks, they are supposed to help people extract the right information to classify the image correctly.",
    "A factor closely related to AI accuracy is AI uncertainty.",
    "Saliency maps can have a paradoxical relation with AI uncertainty, prompting people to contradict the AI in the wrong situations (Cau et al., 2023).",
    "That is, saliency maps led people to agree more with unconfident AI predictions but less with confident AI predictions compared to a baseline without XAI.",
